cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with visual relationship detection, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel technique for learning conditional triplet distributions, which involves the use of tensor decompositions. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves modeling the probability of selecting an object proposal pair and includes a relation triplet prior in the model, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
